# nRF52840 — PIR Motion Sensor

Zephyr BLE PIR motion sensor running on ESP32-C3 DevKit. Advertises motion event count and battery SOC. Supports USB (bench) and UART (battery) console profiles.

## Hardware

- **MCU:** ESP32-C3 DevKitM
- **Board:** `esp32c3_devkitm`
- **Interface:** PIR input, BLE advertising

## Source Files

| File | Description |
|:-----|:------------|
| `src/main.c` | BLE advertising, PIR event counting |
| `src/max17048.c` | MAX17048 fuel gauge driver |
| `src/flash_log.c` | Flash-backed event logging |
| `src/fatal_hook.c` | Fatal error handler |

## Environment Setup

```bash
source ~/zephyrproject/.venv/bin/activate
export ZEPHYR_BASE=~/zephyrproject/zephyr
```

## Build

**Bench USB — halt on crash (JTAG attached):**
```bash
west build -p always -b esp32c3_devkitm \
  -d ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/pir/build_esp \
  ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/pir \
  -- -DDTC_OVERLAY_FILE=boards/esp32c3_devkitm_usb.overlay \
     -DOVERLAY_CONFIG=usb_debug.conf \
     -DCONFIG_DEBUG=y
```

**Bench USB — log + reset:**
```bash
west build -p always -b esp32c3_devkitm \
  -d ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/pir/build_esp \
  ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/pir \
  -- -DDTC_OVERLAY_FILE=boards/esp32c3_devkitm_usb.overlay \
     -DOVERLAY_CONFIG=usb_debug.conf
```

**Battery deployment — UART console:**
```bash
west build -p always -b esp32c3_devkitm \
  -d ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/pir/build_esp \
  ~/embedded-iot-hub/nrf52840/pir \
  -- -DDTC_OVERLAY_FILE=boards/esp32c3_devkitm_uart.overlay \
     -DOVERLAY_CONFIG=uart_debug.conf
```

## Flash

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /mnt/nrf52
sudo mount /dev/sda /mnt/nrf52
sudo cp build/zephyr/zephyr.uf2 /mnt/nrf52/
sync && sudo umount /mnt/nrf52
```

## Monitor

```bash
minicom -D /dev/ttyACM0 -b 115200
```

## Teardown

```bash
deactivate
```

## Testing

Unit tests run on-host via `native_sim` — no hardware needed.

```bash
rm -rf build_test
west build -b native_sim tests/unit --build-dir build_test
west build -t run --build-dir build_test
```
